- The new `DataStream` class (and `CDataStream` subclass) looks quite straightforward when looking at the commit with `--color-moved=dimmed_zebra`.
- I didn't manually verify the changed instances of `CDataStream`->`DataStream` (yet), as there are quite a few. I _think_ it's reasonable enough to assume that if it compiles, it means the `GetType()` and `GetVersion()` functions are never called on that instance and it can safely be a `DataStream`. The main exception I see to that assumption is if the affected code is in a conditionally compiled block, such as e.g. in [`sighash_tests.cpp`](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/50ac8f57748edd0bf4d42031710a59ebb8068a63/src/test/sighash_tests.cpp#L141), in which case it may only fail with certain configurations.
